@Pawanpreetkaur175 

```
$ skopeo copy --help
Container "IMAGE-NAME" uses a "transport":"details" format.

Flags:
      --additional-tag strings                additional tags (supports docker-archive)
  -a, --all                                   Copy all images if SOURCE-IMAGE is a list
      --authfile string                       path of the authentication file. Default is ${XDG_RUNTIME_DIR}/containers/auth.json
```

(Alternatively, if source and destinations require different credentials, you can provide `--src-authfile` and `--dest-authfile`).

It contains:
```
{
	"auths": {
		"my-example-repo.com": {
			"auth": "base64-encoded<username-for-repo>:<password-for-repo>"
		}
	}
}
```

As per the "help" it will default to `${XDG_RUNTIME_DIR}/containers/auth.json` if not provided.
